      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Alternative turbulence and hemolysis model forms must be evaluated and selection justified through sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model were selected based on literature precedent. Formal model-form uncertainty analysis comparing alternative formulations has not been completed. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs must be characterized with probability distributions and propagated through a formal uncertainty quantification framework.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed for two primary inputs (flow rate, rotational speed). Material property uncertainties (blood viscosity, density) and hemolysis model coefficients were not included in the UQ sweep. Input characterization is incomplete for MRL 5 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sample-to-sample variability in experimental hemolysis measurements must be characterized and reported with sufficient replication.",
      "rationale": "The FDA benchmark dataset provides limited replication (n=3 per operating point). Inter-laboratory variability has not been characterized. Test sample adequacy for MRL 5 statistical requirements has not been formally evaluated."
    },
    {
